[ProMED-mail thanks Robin Hide for sending in this report.

The concern about introduction of chikungunya virus into Queensland with the risk of ongoing local transmission is realistic. As noted above, this area has been experiencing local transmission of dengue viruses this year (2013), so conditions exist to also transmit chikungunya virus should individuals coming from areas of chikungunya virus transmission arrive in Cairns while viremic. It is good to learn that the situation is being monitored.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Queensland can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1kJr. - Mod.TY]

[The 2 mosquito species mentioned can also transmit yellow fever virus, if an infected passenger from an endemic area in Africa or South America should arrive in Queensland. Australia should have a contingency plan in place for that possibility (even if rather remote). - Mod.JW]
